The paper deals with optimization problems on graphs, specifically the problem of finding the maximum independent set reachable from a given independent set by adding or removing vertices one at a time, subject to certain constraints. This problem involves graph theory, algorithms, and complexity theory, which are all covered by the arXiv CS sub-categories of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), and Game Theory (cs.GT). However, since the paper focuses on graph optimization problems, the sub-categories of cs.DS and cs.GT are the most likely, followed by cs.CC, cs.DM, and cs.CG.
